    • Method Detail

      • parameterIterator

        public static com.complexible.common.iterations.Iteration<com.complexible.common.base.Pair<String,String>,IOException> parameterIterator(InputStream theStream,
                                                                                                                         Charset theCharset)
        Returns an Iteration of the key-value pairs found in the InputStream. QueryStringDecoder is normally used to parse the key-value pairs from a URL path or a form encoded body, but in the latter case, that requires all of the content in the body to be read into memory. This will lazily consume the stream returning the key-value pairs as they're found. The downside is that for multi-valued keys, you'll receive multiple key-value pairs for the same key, rather than a key with the list of all values such as you get from QueryStringDecoder.
        Parameters:
        theStream - the form encoded input stream
        theCharset - the charset the streams is encoded with
        Returns:
        an Iteration over the key-value pairs in the stream
